---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Container from '../Container.astro';
import Button from '../Button.astro';
import { t } from '../../i18n/ui';
import { site } from '../../data/site';

// Three-part personal credo (kicker, set apart from the intro).
const epigraph = ['Clarity over comfort', 'Outcomes over output', 'Why before what'];

// Verbatim author copy — do not paraphrase or reorder.
const essay = [
  'Hi, I’m Iulian. Over the past five years, as a Product Manager, I’ve been working on AI-powered clinical decision support software used daily by more than 20,000 clinicians across thousands of NHS general practices, helping to support earlier cancer detection and contributing to the identification of tens of thousands of cancers so far.',
  'Working where a single product decision can touch a patient outcome shaped how I think about the job: solve a real problem, respect the full context, and decide responsibly even when you can’t decide perfectly.',
  'I didn’t start in product. I began in IT as a QA engineer — a deliberate choice, because I wanted to understand how technology actually gets built before trying to decide what we should build. That technical grounding still shapes how I work: I can talk to engineers in their own terms, ask sharper questions, and make more informed calls.',
  'Roadmaps, prioritisation, discovery, stakeholder alignment — these are the craft, and every PM should be fluent in them. But they’re not the point. The real work starts when information is incomplete and priorities compete: bringing clarity, getting people around one shared outcome, and helping the team make a good decision and move. A big part of how I see the role is connecting people and perspectives — because many product problems turn out to be alignment and communication problems rather than purely technical ones.',
  'I’d also rather ship less and change something real. What matters to me is whether the thing we built actually helped the people using it — not how much of it there was.',
  'Right now I’m deliberately moving toward connected hardware — products where software meets the physical world. This site is where I document that journey: what I’m learning about electronics, embedded systems, and IoT, alongside notes on product, books, and the ideas I’m chewing on.',
  'If you’re building something at that intersection — or just want to compare notes on product — I’d be glad to hear from you.',
];
---
<BaseLayout title={t('about.title')}>
  <Container width="prose" class="py-16">
    <!-- Accessible page heading (the visible opening is the portrait + credo). -->
    <h1 class="sr-only">{t('about.title')}</h1>

    <!-- Intro: portrait + personal credo (each line of the credo on its own row) -->
    <div class="flex flex-col-reverse gap-6 sm:flex-row sm:items-start sm:justify-between">
      <div class="space-y-1.5 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-muted sm:text-base" role="doc-epigraph">
        {epigraph.map((part) => <p>{part}</p>)}
      </div>
      {site.photo && (
        <img
          src={site.photo}
          alt="Iulian Malovanyi"
          width="144"
          height="144"
          loading="eager"
          class="h-32 w-32 shrink-0 rounded-2xl border border-line object-cover shadow-[var(--shadow-soft)] sm:h-36 sm:w-36"
        />
      )}
    </div>

    <!-- Essay (uniform body size) -->
    <div class="mt-10 space-y-5 text-[1.05rem] leading-relaxed">
      {essay.map((para) => <p>{para}</p>)}
    </div>

    <!-- Actions -->
    <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3 border-t border-line pt-8">
      {site.cvPath
        ? <Button href={site.cvPath} variant="primary">{t('about.cv.download')}</Button>
        : <Button variant="secondary" class="cursor-default opacity-70">{t('about.cv.soon')}</Button>}
      <Button href={site.linkedin} variant="ghost">{t('cta.connect')}</Button>
    </div>
  </Container>
</BaseLayout>
